Ferroglobe PLC Key Developments

Ferroglobe PLC Appoints Deloitte LLP as Auditor
Jun 29 17
Ferroglobe PLC announced at the AGM held on June 28, 2017, the shareholders appointed Deloitte LLP as auditor of the company to hold office from the conclusion of the Annual General Meeting until the conclusion of the next general meeting at which accounts are laid before the company.


Ferroglobe PLC, Annual General Meeting, Jun 28, 2017
Jun 2 17
Ferroglobe PLC, Annual General Meeting, Jun 28, 2017, at 13:00 Coordinated Universal Time. Location: Brown’s Hotel, 19 Dover Street London United Kingdom Agenda: To approve the directors’ and auditor’s reports and the accounts of the company for the financial year ended 31 December 2016; to consider the the directors’ remuneration report (excluding that part containing the directors’ remuneration policy) for the year ended 31 December 2016; to consider the re-election of directors; to appoint Deloitte LLP as auditor to hold office from the conclusion of the Annual General Meeting until the conclusion of the next general meeting; to authorise the director to purchase own shares; to authorise the company to make political donations; and to consider the amendment of the company’s articles of association.


Ferroglobe PLC Announces Board Changes
Jun 2 17
Ferroglobe PLC announced that Tomás García Madrid has resigned as director of the Board, effective May 30, 2017. In addition, the Board has unanimously decided that it would be in the interests of the company to appoint Pedro Larrea Paguaga, the Chief Executive Officer of Ferroglobe, to the Board. The Board has resolved that, upon approval of the proposed amendments to the Articles, Mr. Larrea Paguaga will be appointed to the Board immediately on conclusion of the AGM and would hold office until the next AGM. As a director, Mr. Larrea Paguaga would be subject to re-election in the same manner as the other Board members.


