Energy

 



Ferroglobe is the largest independent hydroelectric energy producer in Spain, with 14 power plants in Spain and France. The combined installed capacity of those plants is 209 MW with an annual average production of 650 million KWh. The group also has two reservoirs with a combined capacity of 120 hm³.




